results.name: Suspected permutation of natural numbers: a(n) = A255070(A269363(n)).
comment: Lexicographically first injection of natural numbers beginning with a(1)=1 such that for all n >= 1, A091067(a(n))*A091067(a(n+1)) is a fibbinary number (A003714), i.e., has no adjacent 1's in its base-2 representation.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..13217
Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
program: (define (A269368 n) (A269367 (- n))) ;; This returns inverse values of A269367 from its hidden cache.
xref: Left inverse: A269368 (also the right inverse if this is a permutation of natural numbers).
